locality.
</emphasis>
“ 
<collectingRegion box="[382,505,830,854]" country="Peru" name="Amazonas" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Amazones</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[521,589,830,854]" name="Peru" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Pérou</collectingCountry>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BF87CDC10BFFEEFF32FDA7C7C9FA91:8EC96000C10BFFEEFDF8FCDDC00FFCB5" box="[605,780,829,854]" country="Peru" county="Caballococha" latitude="-3.9" longLatPrecision="1307" longitude="-70.51667" municipality="Caballo Cocha" name="Cavallo-Cocho" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" stateProvince="Amazones">Cavallo-Cocho</location>
”. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BF87CDC10BFFEEFF32FDA7C7C9FA91:8EC96000C10BFFEEFC80FCDDC0CDFCB5" box="[805,974,829,854]" country="Peru" county="Caballococha" latitude="-3.9" longLatPrecision="1307" longitude="-70.51667" municipality="Caballo Cocha" name="Cavallo-Cocho" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" stateProvince="Amazones">Cavallo-Cocho</location>
is actually the town known as 
<collectingMunicipality pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Caballo Cocha</collectingMunicipality>
or more properly 
<collectingCounty box="[436,589,865,890]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Caballococha</collectingCounty>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[607,681,865,890]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" precision="925" value="-3.9">3°54'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[695,796,866,890]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" precision="925" value="-70.51667">70°31'W</geoCoordinate>
)
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1638471457" country="Peru" location="river Amazon" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Loreto" typeStatus="holotype">
It is located on the right bank of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BF87CDC10BFFEEFF32FDA7C7C9FA91:8EC96000C10BFFEEFB45FC81C67EFC99" box="[1248,1405,865,890]" country="Peru" name="river Amazon" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" stateProvince="Loreto">river Amazon</location>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[151,226,902,925]" country="Peru" name="Loreto" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Loreto</collectingRegion>
department, eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[459,514,902,925]" name="Peru" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Peru</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,721,1394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,419,937,962]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Taxonomic status.</emphasis>
A junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cramer, 1775)" authorityName="Cramer" authorityYear="1775" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[819,1119,937,962]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronis">
<emphasis box="[819,927,938,961]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">H. cronis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cramer" box="[947,1111,937,962]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" refString="Cramer, P. (1775 - 1782) De uitlandische Kapellen voorkomende in de drie Waereld-Deelen Asia, Africa en America. Papillons exotiques des trois parties du monde l'Asie, l'Afrique et l'Amerique. Vol. 2. S. J. Baalde &amp; J. Van Schoonhoven &amp; Comp., Amsteldam &amp; B. Wild, Utrecht, 151 pp., pls. 97 - 192." type="book chapter" year="1775">Cramer, 1775</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon was originally described as a species and treated as such by 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[670,823,973,998]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" refString="Miller, J. Y. (1995) Castniidae. In: Heppner, J. B. (Ed.), Checklist: Part 2. Hyblaeoidea-Pyraloidea-Tortricoidea. Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Association for Tropical Lepidoptera / Scientific Publishers, Gainesville, pp. 133 - 137, 176 - 177." type="book chapter" year="1995">Miller (1995)</bibRefCitation>
but subsequently revised to a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[1331,1400,974,997]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronis">
<emphasis box="[1331,1400,974,997]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">cronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamas" box="[151,311,1009,1034]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" refString="Lamas, G. (1995) A critical review of J. Y. Miller's checklist of the Neotropical Castniidae (Lepidoptera). Revista peruana de Entomologia, 37, 73 - 87." type="journal article" year="1995">Lamas (1995)</bibRefCitation>
. It is considered here to be merely a variant individual of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[956,1060,1010,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronis">
<emphasis box="[956,1060,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">H. cronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and therefore a junior subjective synonym of that taxon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="264" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,721,1394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1081,1106]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Distribution.</emphasis>
Apart from the 
<typeStatus box="[553,651,1081,1106]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">holotype</typeStatus>
the only similar specimen we know of is a male in RW recently acquired from Picuroyacu (
<geoCoordinate box="[458,532,1118,1142]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" precision="925" value="-3.6166668">3°37'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[543,643,1117,1142]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" precision="925" value="-73.26667">73°16'W</geoCoordinate>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[663,741,1118,1141]" country="Peru" name="Loreto" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Loreto</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[751,806,1118,1141]" name="Peru" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="264" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,721,1394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1153,1178]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Discussion.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[393,491,1153,1178]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">holotype</typeStatus>
appeared to be unique until a specimen was recently acquired by RW (see above). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="cronis (Cramer" authorityYear="1775" box="[151,392,1189,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Haemonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cronis" subSpecies="cronis">
<emphasis box="[151,392,1189,1213]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Haemonides c. cronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from Iquitos, 
<collectingRegion box="[659,737,1190,1213]" country="Peru" name="Loreto" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Loreto</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[747,799,1190,1213]" name="Peru" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[814,888,1189,1214]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" precision="925" value="-3.75">3°45'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[899,998,1189,1214]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" precision="925" value="-73.25">73°15'W</geoCoordinate>
), which is only 
<quantity box="[1175,1253,1189,1214]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" unit="km" value="300.0">300km</quantity>
west of the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1190,1214]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Houlbert" authorityYear="1917" box="[271,422,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Castnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odila">
<emphasis box="[271,422,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Castnia odila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is also a small series of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[771,874,1226,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Haemonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronis">
<emphasis box="[771,874,1226,1249]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">H. cronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Iquitos in RW, however, the male phenotype is identical to that of typical 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[471,540,1262,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Haemonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronis">
<emphasis box="[471,540,1262,1285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">cronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and bears no resemblance to the 
<typeStatus box="[913,961,1262,1286]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Houlbert" authorityYear="1917" box="[998,1056,1261,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Castnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odila">
<emphasis box="[998,1056,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">odila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,721,1394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
In the past there has been some confusion over the name with most people (particularly dealers) using the name to refer to all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="cronis (Cramer" authorityYear="1775" box="[371,580,1333,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Haemonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cronis" subSpecies="cronis">
Peruvian 
<emphasis box="[477,580,1334,1357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">H. cronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
